### Form-Urlencoded

```dart
final dio = {{DIO_CREATE_FORM}};
// Content-Type header is set automatically
```

## Dio Initialization

| Way                            | When to use                        |
|--------------------------------|------------------------------------|
| `{{DIO_CREATE}}`              | JSON (default)                     |
| `{{DIO_CREATE_FORM}}`          | Form-urlencoded                    |
| `{{DIO_FORM_INSTANCE}}`        | Singleton with interceptors pre-wired |

`{{DIO_CREATE}}` ships with:
- `LogInterceptor` (responseBody, error, requestBody; uses `printWrapped`).
- `QueuedInterceptorsWrapper`:
  - `onRequest`: adds `Authorization: Bearer ...` (via `_headerOption` callback if set, empty fallback).
  - `onResponse`: calls `_callbackResponse` hook if set.
  - `onError`:
    - Network/timeout → sets message to `{{I18N_CLASS}}.warningNotConnectInternet`.
    - 401 → retries once (clones request).
    - 404 → sets message to `{{I18N_CLASS}}.warningNotFound`.
    - Else → `initException(error)` (parses `data['title']`/`['message']`/`['msg']`/`['detail']`).

## Request / Response Models

```dart
class XxxRequest {
  final int page;
  final int size;
  XxxRequest({required this.page, required this.size});
  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() => {'page': page, 'size': size};
}

class XxxResponse {
  final List<XxxModel>? data;
  final int? status;
  final String? message;

  XxxResponse({this.data, this.status, this.message});

  factory XxxResponse.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => XxxResponse(
        data: (json['data'] as List?)
            ?.map((e) => XxxModel.fromJson(e as Map<String, dynamic>))
            .toList(),
        status: json['status'] as int?,
        message: json['message'] as String?,
      );
}
```

## Error Handling in Provider

```dart
} on {{DIO_EXCEPTION}} catch (e) {
  // DioOption already parsed the message — e.message is ready to use
  errorMessage = e.message ?? {{I18N_CLASS}}.warningNotConnectInternet;
  {{M_SHOW_ERROR}};
} catch (e) {
  errorMessage = e.toString();
  {{M_SHOW_ERROR}};
}
```

## Loading Counter

`{{LOADING_INTERCEPTOR}}` (enabled by default in `DioOption`) calls `{{LOADING_HUB}}.inc()`/`dec()` on every request/response. To suppress per-call:

```dart
await client.post(
  '/api/xxx',
  data: req,
  options: {{LOADING_SUPPRESS}},
);
```

## DO / DON'T

| DO                                              | DON'T                                           |
|-------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| Return typed model (already parsed)              | Return raw `Response<Map<String, dynamic>>`      |
| `errorMessage = e.message` (already parsed)     | Re-parse `e.response?.data['message']` in provider |
| Endpoint as string literal in service (TODO: extract) | Hardcode URL in widget                    |
| `req.toJson()` for body                         | Build Map inline and pass directly to Dio        |
| Catch `{{DIO_EXCEPTION}}` in provider           | Catch generic `Exception` in service (masks bugs) |
| Use `{{DIO_CREATE}}` for new features          | Create fresh `Dio()` (loses interceptors)      |

## Review Checklist

- [ ] Method returns typed model (not raw `Response`).
- [ ] `client` uses `get/post/put/delete/patch` directly (no manual `RequestOptions` construction).
- [ ] `{{DIO_EXCEPTION}}` caught in provider, not in service.
- [ ] Endpoint has a comment (TODO: move to a Routes/Url constant class).
- [ ] `req.toJson()` used for body (not inline Map).
- [ ] NEVER instantiate `Dio()` directly — always go through `{{DIO_CREATE}}`.
